Module com.example.notesmanager
Package com.example.notesmanager

Class Notebook

java.lang.Object
com.example.notesmanager.Notebook
public class Notebook extends Object
Represents a Notebook in the application. A Notebook contains a list of Binders.

  • Constructor Details

    • Notebook

      public Notebook(User user)
      Constructs a Notebook object for the given user.

      This constructor initializes the userID with the ID of the given user. It also initializes the binders list by calling the fetchAllBinders method, which retrieves all binders associated with the user from the database.

      Parameters:
      user - The User object representing the owner of this notebook.

    • fetchAllNotebookContent

      public ResultSet fetchAllNotebookContent()
      Fetches all content related to the Notebook from the database. This includes information about binders, tabs, and notes associated with the user. The method performs a select operation on the database with multiple left joins to retrieve the required data. The result of the select operation is returned as a ResultSet.
      Returns:
      A ResultSet containing all content related to the Notebook.

    • setNotebookContent

      public void setNotebookContent()
      Sets the content of the Notebook by fetching all related content from the database. This method is a shorthand for calling setNotebookContent with a null argument, which means it fetches all content without any label filter.

    • setNotebookContent

      public void setNotebookContent(String labelNameFilter)
      Sets the content of the Notebook by fetching all related content from the database. The method fetches all content related to the Notebook and iterates over the ResultSet. For each row in the ResultSet, it checks if the binder ID, tab ID, and note ID correspond to new entities. If they do, it creates new Binder, Tab, and Note objects and adds them to the appropriate lists. If an exception occurs during this process, it prints the error to the console.

    • createBinder

      public Binder createBinder(String binderName, int binderColorID)
      Creates a new Binder with the specified name and color ID. It inserts the new binder into the database, and then returns the new Binder object.
      Parameters:
      binderName - The name for the new Binder.
      binderColorID - The color ID for the new Binder.
      Returns:
      The new Binder object.

    • deleteBinder

      public int deleteBinder(int binderID)
      Deletes the binder with the specified ID from this notebook. This method first prints the details of the operation to the console. Then, it calls the delete method of the DatabaseManager class to perform the operation.
      Parameters:
      binderID - The ID of the binder to delete.
      Returns:
      The result of the database delete operation.
